- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with language processing, specifically TTS systems that map linguistic features into an acoustic representation.
- cs.LG (Learning): The paper proposes a new approach to improve the quality of TTS voices using problem-agnostic speech embeddings, which involves machine learning techniques.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to improve the quality of TTS voices using problem-agnostic speech embeddings, which involves artificial intelligence techniques.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although less likely, the paper could also be related to computer vision as it deals with generating audible waveforms from linguistic features.
